definitions.definition: The dry, leafy or stringy exterior of certain vegetables or fruits, which must be removed before eating the meat inside
definitions.example: A coconut has a very thick husk.

definitions.definition: Any form of useless, dried-up, and subsequently worthless exterior of something
definitions.example: His attorney was a dried-up husk of a man.

definitions.definition: The supporting frame of a run of millstones.
To remove husks from.
To cough, clear one's throat.
To say huskily, to utter in a husky voice.
The act of impinging.
To change the appearance of a place by altering the decor.
To refurbish.
A sign made without words; a beck.
A children's game similar to hide and seek in which children who have been "caught" may escape if they see another hider beckon to them.
To wave or nod to somebody with the intention to make the person come closer.
To seem attractive and inviting
To wander in mind or intellect; to be delirious; to talk or act irrationally; to be wild, furious, or raging.
To speak or write wildly or incoherently.
To talk with unreasonable enthusiasm or excessive passion or excitement; followed by about, of, or (formerly) on.
To rush wildly or furiously.
To attend a rave (dance party).
An Italian grape-based spirit of between 80 and 100 proof, made from the distillation of pomace.
A variety or serving of grappa.
To create (blaze) a new trail that others can then follow
Resembling a trailblazer; innovative or pioneering.
To draw again.
definitions.example: The treaty proposed to redraw the border lines between the nations.

definitions.definition: To bejewel; to decorate or bedeck with jewels or gems.
Set with jewels
Negotiation to resolve differences conducted by some impartial party.
The act of intervening for the purpose of bringing about a settlement.
To place an object in tension, to pull or place strain on.
definitions.example: We tensioned the cable until it snapped.

definitions.definition: In tension; strained or pulled on.
A particular instance of haunting; a ghostly habitation.
definitions.example: During the haunting, strange voices and noises were heard and objects flew off tables.
